just to have you let him go.

92
00:06:56,889 --> 00:06:58,779
Why didn't you tell me
Darla was pregnant?

93
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:02,980
- You're supposed to kill them.
- She sacrificed herself.

94
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:06,329
Darla did your job for you.
At least one is dust.

95
00:07:07,089 --> 00:07:09,899
Angel's demise will be
a great deal more painful.

96
00:07:10,089 --> 00:07:15,040
You use words like "death,"
"no mercy," but I haven't seen bupkes.

97
00:07:16,089 --> 00:07:18,720
Listen to me.
We've got prophecies to fulfill.

98
00:07:19,089 --> 00:07:21,620
We don't need some deep,
dark plan for Angel.

99
00:07:22,089 --> 00:07:24,860
You put a stake in him,
you watch him go poof.

100
00:07:25,689 --> 00:07:28,009
Step one is getting rid
of these minions.

101
00:07:28,689 --> 00:07:32,019
No, step one is poof,
and then there are no more steps.

102
00:07:32,290 --> 00:07:35,939
We can't get rid of the grapplers.
I signed a two-week contract.

103
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:38,209
You don't wanna piss them off.

104
00:07:38,889 --> 00:07:41,519
They're soulless beasts,
bred to maim and kill.

105
00:07:42,490 --> 00:07:45,399
Maim and kill.
Two more words I like.

106
00:07:45,490 --> 00:07:48,019
You'll need them,
unless your painful plan is...

107
00:07:49,089 --> 00:07:52,459
...to kill Angel with candy clowns
and marshmallow pies.

108
00:07:56,290 --> 00:07:57,759
What's happening?

109
00:07:58,689 --> 00:08:02,339
- I need more than fighters.
- They're choking! Know the Heimlich?

110
00:08:02,889 --> 00:08:06,439
I can't do it in this dimension,
my arms will go through them.

111
00:08:07,089 --> 00:08:08,600
What did you do?

112
00:08:08,889 --> 00:08:10,959
- I poisoned their drink.
- Why?

113
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:14,870
I don't need mercenaries
who kill for anyone willing to pay.

114
00:08:15,490 --> 00:08:18,089
I need warriors who will die
for my cause.

115
00:08:23,290 --> 00:08:24,829
Like that.

116
00:08:25,689 --> 00:08:30,149
Great. So step one is, I'm stuck
with four costly and dead demons.

117
00:08:31,089 --> 00:08:32,389
What's step two?

118
00:08:32,889 --> 00:08:35,629
We can find information
using this box.

119
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:38,389
- Correct?
- Yeah.

120
00:08:38,889 --> 00:08:41,289
You won't believe how fast
my connection is.

121
00:08:41,289 --> 00:08:43,460
- What do you want to find?
- Obituaries.

122
00:08:44,370 --> 00:08:46,090
What about the ninja guy?

123
00:08:46,769 --> 00:08:50,029
- The vampire cult killed him.
- There could be more.

124
00:08:50,370 --> 00:08:51,909
The world is a sick place.

125
00:08:52,169 --> 00:08:55,679
There are already three websites
offering money for the baby.

126
00:08:56,370 --> 00:08:59,000
- Fred, help her trace the websites.
- Right.

127
00:08:59,370 --> 00:09:01,440
It's good. Try it, you'll like it.

128
00:09:02,370 --> 00:09:04,019
So good.

129
00:09:10,169 --> 00:09:11,250
See?

130
00:09:12,570 --> 00:09:16,399
Teddy likes it, and I like it too.

131
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:21,419
See?

132
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:31,830
What was that?

133
00:09:32,370 --> 00:09:34,440
Listening to those furies
gives me whiplash.

134
00:09:34,769 --> 00:09:37,159
Thank God they left.
My head was about to pop off.

135
00:09:37,769 --> 00:09:41,320
- Granted, not a big deal.
- That was their spell kicking in?

136
00:09:41,970 --> 00:09:45,690
They put a force field over the hotel.
Nothing can get in or out.

137
00:09:46,169 --> 00:09:48,590
So the baby's safe?
We're all safe, right?

138
00:09:49,169 --> 00:09:52,720
Unless one of those killers
throws a firebomb in at us...

139
00:09:53,370 --> 00:09:57,620
...like they did at your club, which
had a similar safety spell around it.

140
00:09:59,370 --> 00:10:01,860
- Sorry.
- She's right. He won't be safe here.

141
00:10:02,370 --> 00:10:05,950
We can get out. I installed
an emergency exit in the sewers.

142
00:10:06,570 --> 00:10:09,129
A mystical barrier opens
with a password.

143
00:10:09,570 --> 00:10:13,190
- Pylean word for "hedgehog."
- Oh. Oh!

144
00:10:13,769 --> 00:10:15,840
It means something
different in English?

145
00:10:16,169 --> 00:10:19,009
We'll have to use it.
The baby needs to see a doctor.

146
00:10:19,769 --> 00:10:21,840
What? He's not sick.

147
00:10:22,169 --> 00:10:25,470
- Does he look sick?
- No, but he needs his newborn checkup.

148
00:10:26,370 --> 00:10:30,159
The baby book says that he's supposed
to have a vitamin K shot...

149
00:10:30,570 --> 00:10:34,500
...and a PKU test after he's born.
Are you gonna circumcise?

150
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:39,559
I think he heard you.

151
00:10:39,570 --> 00:10:43,190
Are there fluorescent lights in here?
I keep hearing this hum.

152
00:10:43,769 --> 00:10:47,909
Plus, fluorescents, green light,
green skin, it's all bad.

153
00:10:49,769 --> 00:10:53,529
I'll take the blank stares
as a big, fat no.

154
00:10:53,970 --> 00:10:54,980
- Gunn?
- Yeah?

155
00:10:55,769 --> 00:10:57,309
I'm in a war,
I'll need serious firepower.

156
00:10:57,570 --> 00:10:59,500
- Beyond swords and spears?
- Way beyond.

157
00:10:59,970 --> 00:11:01,580
- Leave it to me.
- Thanks.

158
00:11:01,769 --> 00:11:04,539
- We getting to the websites?
- Not yet.

159
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:08,740
Normally, we'd hack into the e-mail
and trace the relays.

160
00:11:08,970 --> 00:11:11,710
- But they're using remailers.
- Which means?

161
00:11:12,570 --> 00:11:14,850
There's no direct I.D.
It'll take time.

162
00:11:14,970 --> 00:11:17,039
We don't have it.
Are those all the names?

163
00:11:17,970 --> 00:11:21,159
Working on other leads.
We're all doing the best we can.

164
00:11:21,570 --> 00:11:22,940
- Do better.
- Angel.

165
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:24,570
I promised his mother.

166
00:11:24,570 --> 00:11:27,730
No one is gonna put their hands
on this child.

167
00:11:29,370 --> 00:11:30,700
No one.

168
00:11:32,409 --> 00:11:35,600
"No one is going to put
their hands on this child."

169
00:11:36,009 --> 00:11:37,759
Is this meant to be ironic?

170
00:11:38,409 --> 00:11:42,909
According to our highly, and I'm now
thinking overpaid, translators...

171
00:11:43,809 --> 00:11:48,340
...the Nyazian scroll said the child
would never be born, yet here he is.

172
00:11:49,210 --> 00:11:51,840
A technicality.
Darla died during childbirth.

173
00:11:52,210 --> 00:11:53,960
Dusted during childbirth.

174
00:11:54,610 --> 00:11:56,500
Our sources say she staked herself...

175
00:11:57,009 --> 00:12:00,240
...leaving the baby alive
but never actually born.

176
00:12:00,610 --> 00:12:04,539
Macduff was from his mother's womb.
Untimely ripped.

177
00:12:05,409 --> 00:12:06,610
Clever loophole.

178
00:12:06,610 --> 00:12:10,259
We could use those scroll writers
in Contracts and Negotiations.

179
00:12:11,409 --> 00:12:13,480
We have to get that baby.

180
00:12:13,809 --> 00:12:16,019
He has a knack
for stating the obvious.

181
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:19,299
I have a tactical team working
on intercept scenarios.

182
00:12:19,809 --> 00:12:22,409
Lilah would have thought of that,
given time.

183
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:25,440
Moving on, children.

184
00:12:25,809 --> 00:12:28,409
I want everything there is
on this character.

185
00:12:29,409 --> 00:12:31,899
He slaughtered some
of our best-trained men.

186
00:12:32,409 --> 00:12:35,009
- He's gonna be a problem.
- We're locating him.

187
00:12:35,409 --> 00:12:38,179
Preferably before he locates us.

188
00:12:39,009 --> 00:12:42,100
Now, that's a cute little baby.
Yes, you are.

189
00:12:42,610 --> 00:12:45,419
And your daddy is a vampire
with a soul.

190
00:12:46,210 --> 00:12:49,330
And sometimes he reverts
to a creature of pure evil...

191
00:12:49,809 --> 00:12:52,019
...who could rip your tiny throat out.

192
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:53,960
Yes, he does.

193
00:12:57,009 --> 00:13:01,720
I like kids. The senior partners took
mine before I really got to know them.

194
00:13:02,409 --> 00:13:03,669
Turn it up.

195
00:13:06,610 --> 00:13:07,940
Turn it down.

196
00:13:09,610 --> 00:13:11,049
Teddy isn't crying.

197
00:13:12,610 --> 00:13:13,809
Do you see Teddy crying?

198
00:13:13,809 --> 00:13:18,159
Teddy isn't crying. Do you see
Teddy crying? No, he's not crying.

199
00:13:22,809 --> 00:13:25,409
Come on, kid, you gotta
give me something here.

200
00:13:25,809 --> 00:13:28,340
All right, last-ditch effort.

201
00:13:56,409 --> 00:13:58,509
Here, let me give it a try, huh?

202
00:14:25,210 --> 00:14:27,419
He doesn't like Smokey Robinson
and the Miracles?

203
00:14:28,210 --> 00:14:30,460
- You said he had a soul.
- You know what?

204
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:33,700
You're fed. You're changed.
I hold you, you cry.

205
00:14:34,210 --> 00:14:37,299
I put you down, you cry.
What do you want me to do?

206
